{"id":"1205.6117","submitter":"Anders Bengtsson","authors":"Anders K. H. Bengtsson","title":"Systematics of Higher-spin Light-front Interactions","comments":"39 pages, Extended version of contribution to the XVII European\n  Workshop on String Theory, Padua, 5-9 September 2011. Minor corrections to\n  formulas (7.11),(8.1), (8.3), (8.10), (9.4), (9.9) and (9.18). Updated with\n  two references (page 17) about resummation formulas and quartic vertices","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th math-ph math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The original cubic interaction terms for higher spin gauge fields in four\ndimensions and their reformulation using Fock space vertex operators is\nreviewed. As a new result, the complete list of all cubic vertex functions in\nD=4 is derived. It is observed, contrary to what would have been expected, that\nthe non-linear dynamical Poincar\\'e transformations do not restrict the cubic\ninteractions beyond what is required by kinematics. The role of the SU(1,1)\nalgebra of tracelessness constraints is clarified. It is shown that higher spin\nfields couple non-minimally to gravity at the cubic level in D=4 light-front\ndynamics. Based on a detailed analysis of the structure of the light-front\nPoincar\\'e algebra, the formalism is then generalized to all orders in the\ninteraction. The interacting theory, being a deformation of the free theory,\ntakes the form of a strongly homotopy Lie algebra. It is conjectured that the\nensuing recursive equations, if they can be explicitly solved, will encode all\ninteraction data into a denumerable set of functions of p+, the overall\ntransverse momentum structure being fixed already at the kinematical level.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 May 2012 20:39:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 25 Mar 2014 22:27:38 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 21 Sep 2016 21:20:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-23